104dfa0d6d70650b381b6c2f4ae8d63cc56c7921d135&width=800&height=450&smart=false&focal=642%2C85", "https://gray-kswo-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/WPNGAJ47DBE5FBB5CAPAFKSPGU.png?auth=7ef1f4e2827ed675844f5b795195d6a286b03ce0fb4435bf1fc692ccf6183d7c&width=800&height=450&smart=false&focal=632%2C375", "https://gray-kswo-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/https%3A%2F%2Fdo0bihdskp9dy.cloudfront.net%2F12-02-2025%2Ft_5ca254a963e642e4b85059e8fb051cc7_name_file_1280x720_2000_v3_1_.jpg?auth=1605de9bd2de8deacb0d62179d96483f5fa496d2f959b5b26dd6e2c4dd10d6de&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-kswo-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/https%3A%2F%2Fdo0bihdskp9dy.cloudfront.net%2F12-02-2025%2Ft_6bb6c224d77d4309a215feeb66c0fc51_name_file_1280x720_2000_v3_1_.jpg?auth=a5fb8d672477c3162b4c5b079f3abd2ea222347281a88da2d9ec2deac5f8d1a1&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-kswo-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/2AV2T36KCREKPBOD3MKN66Q4T4.png?auth=f7bed6f2eb707fde7f0fcaf488c47b08176c9751d847e8e4fcb3a2d65425293a&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-kswo-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/YLV64OV3KREXTKEGQRGL7PUJWY.jpg?auth=ad550023c8afbe1581ca8c2a9f208bd0a0b4faa055fdb7ed430dafce20adcaf7&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-kswo-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/MRJKQHYIRVG25DO6H3WUW4NYTQ.jpeg?auth=2751ca18993de5fee441d26ef777a36ae4610adfd459337f029176634f4afb2d&width=800&height=450&smart=true"], "publication-date": "2024-08-09", "text": "LAWTON, Okla. (KSWO) - The Lawton Police Department is partnering with a local homeland for the annual ‘Bagging with Badges’ event.\n\nFrom 9 a.m. to 1 p.m., officers with LPD will work with athletes to bag groceries to raise money for the upcoming Special Olympics.\n\nLPD Public Information Officer Charles Whittington says this event also serves as a way to build connections between officers and civilians.\n\n“Come out, go grocery shopping, meet some police officers,” he said. “This is a great way for officers to be able to give back to communities and organizations and for people to realize there are people behind the badge and not just a police officer.”\n\nWhittington this is just one of several events the department participates in to raise money for Special Olympic athletes.\n\nIf you’d like to donate, you can catch officers and athletes at the Homeland location on 6734 NW Cache Road\n\nCopyright 2024 KSWO. All rights reserved.", "title": "LPD partners with Homeland for ‘Bagging and Badges’ event to raise money for Special Olympics", "top-image": "https://gray-kswo-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/CBKKASZ4VRBFHDUYQT7TWBGYGE.png?auth=2f0ecbe83e77a801b187da764031754c44cdc5b3677a2336a747d9a256d11cfc&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "domain": "www.kswo.com", "lang": "en", "author": "", "description": "The Lawton Police Department is partnering with a local homeland for the annual ‘Bagging with Badges’ event.", "keywords": "lpd,lawton police,police,lawton police department,southwest oklahoma,oklahoma,homeland,lawton,good news,charity,7news,kswo,events"}